Subject: New circulars and information for local associations 3-9 February 2006



New circulars and information for local associations 3-9 February 2006



LA/7715 -- Nominations to the academic-related staff committee

This circular contains details of candidates for election to the
academic-related staff annual meeting at the 2006 annual meeting, to be
held on 2 March 2006. Four nominations were received to the vacancies that
will exist from the date of the annual meeting, and the annual meeting will
be asked to declare the candidates elected from that date.

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/html/la7715.html

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/rtf/la7715.rtf



 LA/7714 -- Motions to the 2006 academic-related staff annual meeting

This circular sets out motions from LAs and the academic-related staff
committee for consideration at the 2006 Academic-related staff annual
meeting, to be held on Thursday 2 March 2006. Full details of the annual
meeting were set out in LA/7699, sent out in January and further
information is available at http://www.aut.org.uk/index.cfm?articleid=1314.

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/html/la7714.html

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/rtf/la7714.rtf



LA/7713 -- Report of the Fixed-term staff committee to the 2006 annual
meeting

This circular sets out the report of the AUT fixed-term staff committee on
their work over the last year. The report is a helpful basis for LAs to
consider motions to the 2006 fixed-term staff annual meeting to direct AUT
work on fixed-term issues. LAs are reminded that the deadline for
registering delegates, submission of motions and nominations to committee
vacancies is Monday 6 March 2006. Full details of the annual meeting were
set out in LA/7701 sent out in January and further information, including
an agenda for the annual meeting and the priorities for the committee's
work in the forthcoming year are available at
http://www.aut.org.uk/index.cfm?articleid=1316.

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/html/la7713.html

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/rtf/la7713.rtf



Reminder: Women's annual meeting

LA/7702, sent out in January, gave full details of the women's annual
meeting, to be held on Thursday 23 March 2006. LAs are reminded to consider
motions for submission, register delegates and canvass for nominations to
vacancies on the committee by the deadline of Monday 27 February. Further
information is available on the AUT website at
http://www.aut.org.uk/index.cfm?articleid=1317

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/html/la7702.html

http://www.aut.org.uk/circulars/rtf/la7702.rtf



Briefing meeting for LA presidents, Thursday 23 February 2006

The result of the current industrial action ballot will be announced on
Friday 17 February. This meeting will form an important opportunity to hear
an update on pay negotiations and discuss any industrial action strategies.
It is therefore important that your LA is represented at this meeting and
if your LA President is unable to attend, you are encouraged to ensure that
another LA committee member attends. A registration form and further
information is available at http://www.aut.org.uk/index.cfm?articleid=696



AUT/NATFHE brain drain conference

On 23 March 2006 AUT and NATFHE will be hosting an international
development conference on the brain drain in African higher education. The
conference will examine the findings of the union brain drain project and
discuss action points for trade unions, NGOs, universities and government.
It is open to all academic and academic-related staff as well as NGOs and
policy-makers. Speakers include Dr John Rowett (Association of Commonwealth
Universities), Monique Foulihoux (Education International) and Dr Uwem Ite
(Lancaster University). The conference will be held at the NATFHE
conference centre in London (12-- 16.30pm). An electronic version of the
booking form is available on the AUT website
http://www.aut.org.uk/braindrain . Leaflets, including booking forms, will
also be sent to local associations. Please can you circulate details of the
conference to members.



Links to new circulars are sent to LA secretaries.  If the address to which
this email has been sent is not correct, or for any other changes in the
details of local association officers and contacts please email
mailto:hq@aut.org.uk



Association of University Teacher, Egmont House, 25-31 Tavistock Place,
London Wc1H 9UT

Tel: 020 7670 9700  Fax 020 670 9799 website http://www.aut.org.uk


























